# Cursor AI Global Rules for Bright Leasing Project

## Code Formatting Rules

### Component Structure
Every React component file MUST follow this exact format:

```typescript
/* ************************************************************
                        NOTES
************************************************************ */
// Brief description of the component and its purpose
// Key features and functionality
// Layout and positioning details
/* ************************************************************
                        IMPORTS
************************************************************ */
// All import statements organized here
/* ************************************************************
                        INTERFACES
************************************************************ */
// TypeScript interfaces and type definitions
/* ************************************************************
                        COMPONENTS
************************************************************ */
// Main component declaration
export default function ComponentName({ props }: PropsInterface) {
    /* ************************************************************
                            HOOKS
    ************************************************************ */
    // All React hooks (useState, useEffect, useRef, etc.)
    
    /* ************************************************************
                            FUNCTIONS
    ************************************************************ */
    // All component functions and methods
    
    /* ************************************************************
                            ANIMATION VARIANTS
    ************************************************************ */
    // Framer Motion variants and animations
    
    /* ************************************************************
                            RENDER
    ************************************************************ */
    return (
        // JSX with clear container documentation
        <div>
            {/* ************************************************************
                LEFT CONTAINER - Description
            ************************************************************ */}
            // Left side content
            
            {/* ************************************************************
                RIGHT CONTAINER - Description  
            ************************************************************ */}
            // Right side content
        </div>
    );
}

/* ************************************************************
                        EXPORTS
************************************************************ */
// Export statements (if any additional exports)
```

### Required Sections
- NOTES: Always at the top with component description
- IMPORTS: All import statements
- INTERFACES: TypeScript interfaces (omit if not used)
- COMPONENTS: Main component declaration
- HOOKS: React hooks (omit if not used)
- FUNCTIONS: Component functions (omit if not used)
- ANIMATION VARIANTS: Framer Motion variants (omit if not used)
- RENDER: Main JSX return with container documentation
- EXPORTS: Export statements (omit if not used)

### Container Documentation
Within the RENDER section, always document:
- LEFT CONTAINER: Left side content description
- RIGHT CONTAINER: Right side content description
- Any other major containers with clear descriptions

### Large Container Notes
For major sections within containers, use this format:
```typescript
{/********************** Section Name - Description ************************/}
```

Examples:
- `{/********************** Card 1 - Brand Yellow ************************/}`
- `{/********************** Navigation - Main Menu ************************/}`
- `{/********************** Footer - Contact Info ************************/}`

### Brand Colors
Always use these CSS classes:
- `bg-brand-yellow` for yellow (#FFBD34)
- `bg-brand-teal` for teal (#52BAC7) 
- `bg-brand-black` for black (#121717)
- `bg-brand-cream` for cream (#FCF9F1)
- `text-brand-yellow`, `text-brand-teal`, `text-brand-black`, `text-brand-cream` for text colors

### Typography
Use these global classes:
- `h1` - 48px (ITC Avant Garde Gothic CE Book)
- `h2` - 40px (ITC Avant Garde Gothic CE Book)
- `h3` - 32px (ITC Avant Garde Gothic CE Book)
- `h4` - 26px (ITC Avant Garde Gothic CE Book)
- `p` - 24px (ITC Avant Garde Gothic CE Book, weight 300)
- `.text-small` - 16px (ITC Avant Garde Gothic CE Book, weight 300)

### Animation Standards
- Use Framer Motion for all animations
- Consistent easing: `easeOut` for most transitions
- Duration: 0.6s for standard animations, 0.8s for complex ones
- Always include `useInView` for scroll-triggered animations

### File Organization
- Components in `src/components/`
- Pages in `src/app/`
- Styles in `src/app/globals.css`
- Images in `public/images/`
- Fonts in `public/fonts/`

### Performance Rules
- Keep components under 50 lines when possible
- Use proper memoization with React.memo when needed
- Implement proper loading states
- Use Next.js Image component for all images

### Accessibility
- Always include proper ARIA labels
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Ensure keyboard navigation
- Maintain proper color contrast

## Enforcement
When creating or modifying any component, Cursor AI MUST:
1. Apply this exact format structure
2. Include all relevant sections
3. Document containers within render
4. Use brand colors and typography
5. Follow performance and accessibility guidelines
6. Maintain consistency across all files
